      "comment": "LE CARDINAL (9) was last seen in the Vicbred 2CG Final five-and-a-half months ago having earlier placed in the heats. Likely to have developed with maturity and will be ready to go off a trial placing. ROCKLEIGHS LEGACY (6) comes off the Gold Tiara series at Bathurst where she won a heat before coming from the back row for a midfield finish in the Group 1 final. Draws out and tackles older rivals but will enjoy the class drop. BETTORPATCHMEUP (3) raced parked in winning two back at Hamilton then came from the back for fourth at his most recent appearance at Ballarat. Go well from a good draw. ROBLEN RANGER (10) draws on the back row but scored from a similar barrier two back and owns a good record at this longer distance.",
